Quality Manager

   26 Sep 2013 03:09 PM - Saudi Arabia

   . Quality Manager-T-SYS-MAN-SARI-415g
   Description
   Bombardier Transportation is the number one provider of rail solutions
   in the world. Our business holds the number one global market position
   in eight of the ten markets we service. Our product portfolio includes
   a full range of passenger rail vehicles and we manufacture locomotives,
   bogies, propulsion and rail control solutions.
   At Bombardier, 70,000 employees in 60 countries work together to evolve
   mobility worldwide one good idea at a time. If you have a good idea,
   we'll provide the environment where it will thrive and grow into a
   great product or customer experience. Your ideas are our fuel.
   We are looking for a Quality Manager in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia.
   Your role
   The Project Quality Manager is responsible to develop, implement,
   evaluate, and continually improve quality systems to assure SYS
   processes, products and services meet internal and external
   requirements from proposal preparation through design, manufacturing,
   installation, warranty, and product service life. This position will
   manage Project Quality, Manufacturing Quality, and Non Conforming Cost,
   with a strong focus on quality assurance, root causing, corrective
   action, and continuous improvement.
   Your Key Accountabilities
   - Ensure the department is staffed with qualified, innovative, and
   committed personnel. Develop Quality Engineers to achieve their full
   potential and create a broad knowledge base within the group. Recommend
   salary adjustments. Select and train subordinates, set their objectives
   and review performance.
   - Plan activities of Project Quality personnel and assign people to
   customer-funded and strategic programs to support schedules and
   commitments.
   - Manage the Project Quality group to achieve budgetary project goals.
   Control expenditures. Evaluate, choose, implement and maintain advanced
   computer-aided tools to improve productivity and analysis capability.
   - Maintain open and effective interfaces with engineering,
   manufacturing, project management, supply management, and provide
   support to marketing and field sites as required. Represent BT SYS to
   internal and external customers in a professional and competent manner
   that reflects the commitment and experience of the organization.
   - Lead and continually improve the key quality processes including NCC,
   Corrective Action (CAR/PAR/OFI), Incoming, In-Process, and Final
   Inspection; and support the SEAP/PAP process and the IRIS, ISO, BOS,
   Q6, and CMMI certification efforts.
   - Design and maintain quality control systems, support first article
   inspection and source inspection activities, determine disposition of
   non-conforming material and assign corrective action at the sub-system
   level. Develop, review, and approve Bombardier quality plans that
   communicate quality disciplines and commitments internally, to
   customers and to our products.
   Qualifications
   - Degree in Mechanical or Electrical Engineering or equivalent.
   - 8 years relevant quality and engineering experience.
   - Understand the BT project management processes and tools.
   - Gate review process, project review process.
   - Able to facilitate an FMEA (systems, Design, Process).
   - Strong knowledge of Advanced Product Quality Planning (APQP)
   methodology, involvement experience in a project.
   - Experience in Quality function (SQA, OQA, DQA, IMS).
   - Project auditing, customer communication and management.
   - Good knowledge of the IRIS, ISO, and CMMi standards.
   We thank all applicants for their interest; however, only those under
   consideration will be contacted.
   We are looking for great professionals to join us. For more information
   about our projects, products or if you want to 'meet' with our core
   project teams, please join our group on LinkedIn - Bombardier
   Transportation - The Gulf Network.
